Vol / Page: IV/123
Edition:
Quote: PTERYGOTRIGLA PICTA (Gunther[u-dieresis]). <i>Spotted Gurnard</i>. A rare species in Auckland and Wellington markets. Examples noted in Wellington were received from Napier. Distribution: North Island (unknown south of Napier).
Notes:  Phillipps Notes on the Edible Fishes

