Date: 0/0/1982
Source: Collins Guide
Author: AYLING
Vol / Page: 197
Edition: 1984
Quote: <i>SPOTTED GURNARD Pterygotrigla</i> ... The spotted gurnard is similar to the red gurnard in shape but has larger more [198] protruberant eyes and is usually smaller ... Body colour ... is pink-yellow above with numerous small black spots, and white beneath.
Notes:

